# Coding Conventions

## File & Import Conventions

- Use `@/` alias for project root imports (configured in babel.config.js)
- API modules live in `lib/api/` — one file per domain (e.g. `businessHours.ts`, `services.ts`)
- Zustand stores live in `stores/` — one file per domain with AsyncStorage persist
- Shared components live in `components/`

## Supabase & Data Access

- Always use `getBusinessId()` from `lib/supabase.ts` to scope queries to the current tenant
- Never hardcode business IDs — they come from the `.env` / `BUSINESS_ID` extra config
- API functions return typed data; use existing patterns in `lib/api/` as reference
- Handle loading/error states in hooks or stores, not in screen components directly

## State Management (Zustand)

- Each store uses `persist` middleware with AsyncStorage
- Auth store (`stores/authStore`) gates navigation — check `isHydrated` before routing
- Don't duplicate Supabase data in multiple stores; pick one source of truth

## Navigation (Expo Router)

- Route groups: `(client-tabs)` for clients, `(tabs)` for admins
- Hidden tabs use `href: null` in layout options
- Stack-style sub-routes (e.g. `select-time`, `select-barber`) are nested inside tab groups
- Use `router.replace()` for auth redirects, `router.push()` for normal navigation

## TypeScript

- Define interfaces for all props, API responses, and store shapes
- Export types from where they're defined (e.g. `ThemeColors` from `ThemeProvider.tsx`)
- Prefer `interface` over `type` for object shapes

## Do's and Don'ts

- **DO** use the `useTheme()` / `useColors()` hooks for colors — never hardcode hex values
- **DO** use i18n `t()` function for user-facing strings
- **DO** keep screens relatively thin — extract logic to hooks or API modules
- **DON'T** import directly from `expo-constants` — use `getExpoExtra()` wrapper
- **DO** support RTL layout — the app is Hebrew-first, right-to-left (see ui-design-patterns for details)
- **DON'T** create new Supabase client instances — use the shared one from `lib/supabase.ts`
